<article class="video">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="row">
      <div class="video_large_cover span7 offset1">
        <img src="http://dummyimage.com/665x375/000000/00a2ff" />
      </div>
      <div class="video_info span3">
        <header>
          <h3>Futurama</h3>
          <span>Rating: 4.5/5.0</span>
        </header>
        <p>Pizza boy Philip J. Fry awakens in the 31st century after 1,000 years of cryogenic preservation in this animated series. After he gets a job at an interplanetary delivery service, Fry embarks on ridiculous escapades to make sense of his predicament.</p>
        <div class="actions">
          <a href="" class="btn btn-primary">Watch Now</a>
          <a href="" class="btn">+ My Queue</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>

<section class="reviews container">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="span10 offset1">
      <form action="">
        <fieldset>
          <label>Rate this video</label>
          <select name="">
            <option value="5">5 Stars</option>
            <option value="4">4 Stars</option>
            <option value="3">3 Stars</option>
            <option value="2">2 Stars</option>
            <option value="1">1 Star</option>
          </select>
          <label>Write Review</label>
          <textarea name="" rows="6" class="span6"></textarea>
        </fieldset>
        <fieldset class="actions clearfix">
          <input type="submit" value="Submit" class="btn" />
          <a href="">Cancel</a>
        </fieldset>
        <header>
          <h3>User Reviews (253)</h3>
        </header>
        <ul>
          <% 8.times do %>
            <article class="review">
              <li class="row">
                <div class="span2">
                  Rating: 5 / 5
                  <p>by <a href="">John A. Zoidberg</a></p>
                </div>
                <div class="span8">
                  <p>In my opinion, this is one of the best shows ever made. It's not only funny, but despite being so frequently silly, it's very smart as well. Math, science, history, all get referenced. The best parts of the show are the subtle things, those little things in the background or just on screen for a couple of seconds that just make you laugh out loud if you were paying attention. The writers even appear to have been thinking ahead, because if you play close attention to the first episode, you can see a literal shadow of an event revealed seasons later.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </article>
          <% end %>
        </ul>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
